        <name>7.1.2.2 Classifying matrices</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;p class="HELM_exercise"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Give the size of the following matrices:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol class="HELM_parts"&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;\({@mat1@}\) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] \(\times\) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;[[feedback:prt1]] [[feedback:prt2]]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;\({@mat2@}\) [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]] \(\times\) [[input:ans4]]  [[validation:ans4]]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;[[feedback:prt3]] [[feedback:prt4]]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Find the trace of the following matrices:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol class="HELM_parts"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;\(A={@mat3@}\), \(\text{tr}(A) = \) [[input:ans5]][[validation:ans5]][[feedback:prt5]]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;\(B={@mat4@}\), \(\text{tr}(B) = \) [[input:ans6]][[validation:ans6]][[feedback:prt6]]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>&lt;p&gt;First, we find the size of the first two matrices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol class="HELM_parts"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The matrix&lt;/p&gt;
\[{@mat1@}\]
&lt;p&gt;has {@m1@} rows and {@n1@} columns. Therefore, it is a \({@m1@} \times {@n1@}\) matrix.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The matrix&lt;/p&gt;
\[{@mat2@}\]
&lt;p&gt;has {@m2@} rows and {@n2@} columns. Therefore, it is a \({@m2@} \times {@n2@}\) matrix.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Next, we find the trace of the given matrices. Recall that the trace of a square matrix is the sum of its diagonal entries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol class="HELM_parts"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The matrix&lt;/p&gt;
\[A = {@mat3@}\]
&lt;p&gt;has diagonal entries {@mat3[1][1]@} and {@mat3[2][2]@}. Therefore, its trace is \(\mathrm{tr}(A) = {@mat3[1][1]@} + {@mat3[2][2]@} = {@tamat3@}\).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Similarly, the matrix&lt;/p&gt;
\[B = {@mat4@}\]
&lt;p&gt;has trace \(\mathrm{tr}(B) = {@tamat4@}\).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;</generalfeedback>
